"DAMN RIGHT WE DO!"

You let your anger flow into the phone. "This debt arrangement is economic imperialism! The Americans are charging us interest to pay for equipment we used fighting *their* war in the Pacific! The wharfies - American and Australian - are showing more solidarity than our own government!"

"Every bale of wool, every ton of wheat goes to American banks while Australian workers go hungry. The Taft wharfies understand what Menzies doesn't - this is debt slavery!"

The journalist is scribbling frantically. You can already see tomorrow's headline: "LABOR MP BACKS US STRIKE AGAINST AUSTRALIAN EXPORTS."

Jim Healey is beaming. "That's the stuff, Eddie! The workers will love this!"

But your phone immediately rings again. It's J.J. Cahill, and he's furious.

"WARD! WHAT THE BLOODY HELL DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?!"

**The party leadership will need to respond to your statement...**

