"Labor supports workers' fundamental right to protest exploitative economic arrangements," you say carefully. "The debt repayment scheme places an enormous burden on Australian workers. If American wharfies want to express solidarity, that's their democratic right."

It's a more careful position, but it still signals sympathy for the strike.

The journalist presses: "But isn't this communist sabotage of the Australian economy?"

"It's workers expressing solidarity across national borders," you reply. "That's not communism - that's basic unionism."

Jim Healey looks slightly disappointed, but nods. "Good enough, Eddie. You didn't sell us out."

**The party leadership will need to decide on an official position...**

