"Labor supports Australian workers," you say, choosing your words carefully. "This strike hurts Australian workers more than it helps them. Our economy depends on those exports. Families depend on that income."

"While we appreciate international labor solidarity, we cannot support actions that damage the Australian economy and hurt Australian working families."

The line goes dead. Jim Healey stares at you in disbelief.

"Eddie... what the hell? You just sold out the wharfies!"

"I saved the party from a political disaster," you snap back. "Menzies would crucify us!"

Healey's face hardens. "The wharfies will remember this, Ward. The WWF will remember."

**You've avoided a political crisis, but at what cost?**

