"We don't unload until we get assurances about Australian worker conditions!"

It's a compromise - not a full strike, but a protest action. You're using leverage without completely shutting down the ship.

Harry Bridges nods approvingly. "Smart. We'll drag this out, make noise, get the press involved. Let the world see what this debt scheme is doing."

The *Southern Cross* sits partially unloaded while negotiations drag on.

**This will buy time, but everyone will need to take a position eventually...**

