"We work, but under protest. Slow and steady. And we make damn sure every newspaper in San Francisco knows WHY."

The crew begins unloading, but at a deliberate crawl. Every journalist who'll listen gets an earful about Australian debt slavery. Picket signs go up: "AUSTRALIA DESERVES FAIR TERMS" and "WORKERS NOT BANKERS."

It's symbolic resistance rather than direct action.

Harry Bridges shrugs. "Better than nothing. At least you're making noise."

**The symbolic protest makes a statement without causing economic damage...**

