"We unload. Our job is to move cargo, not make foreign policy."

Harry Bridges looks disappointed. Some of your crew grumble, but they get to work. The *Southern Cross* is unloaded on schedule.

The Australian cargo continues its journey to creditors. The debt gets serviced. The system continues unchanged.

"Sometimes," you mutter to yourself, "solidarity has to take a back seat to practicality."

But you can see the disappointment in the eyes of the more militant men.

**The cargo is unloaded. The crisis is averted. Nothing changes.**

